More than half the world's coral reefs endangered: IUCN BANGKOK, Nov 19 AFP More than 58 percent of the world's coral reefs are endangered because of pollution, the over-harvesting of reef fish and other human factors, the World Conservation Union IUCN said Friday.
Only about 30 percent of the world's coral reefs are healthy, down from 41 percent two years ago, according to a study released Monday that lists global warming as the top threat.
